  "texts": [
    "Accuracy was the most commonly reported metric, followed by F -score, precision, and recall.",
    "A smaller number of studies incorporated fairness-or engagement-related metrics, reflecting an emerging emphasis on ethical and participatory evaluation frameworks in public health sentiment analysis.",
    "Ethical challenges and mitigation strategies in sentiment analysis for public health.",
    "Ethical issue Description of challenge Potential mitigation strategies Consent Infeasibility of obtaining explicit informed consent from large numbers of online users.",
    "Ambiguity of implied consent via Terms of Service (ToS); users often unaware or uncomfortable."
